* KidTask – Task & Reward Management System

KidTask is a Java Swing–based desktop application designed to help children develop responsibility through task management and a reward system. Parents and teachers can assign, approve, and evaluate tasks, while children complete tasks, earn points, and track their progress.

 **Project Purpose

The goal of KidTask is to:

Encourage children to complete daily responsibilities

Provide a structured task approval and rating system

Track progress using points, levels, and dashboards

Apply Object-Oriented Programming principles in a real-world project

 ** User Roles & Features
 -Child

View assigned tasks

Filter tasks (today / this week / all)

Mark tasks as completed

View completed tasks and ratings

Earn points and level up

View and manage wishes

 -Parent

Create and assign tasks to children

Approve or reject completed tasks

Rate tasks (1–5)

View child progress and points

Manage wishes

 -Teacher

Approve or reject completed tasks

Rate tasks (1–5)

View dashboard summary

View statistics (approved vs rejected tasks)

Visualize data using charts

 ** Main Functionalities

Task assignment and tracking

Task approval & rating system

Points and level system for children

Role-based dashboards (Child / Parent / Teacher)

Persistent data storage using JSON

Visual dashboard with charts
 ** How to Run the Project

Open the project in IntelliJ IDEA

Make sure Java SDK (Java 17 or compatible) is installed

Run the MainApp.java file

Select a role from the Role Selection screen

 ** Object-Oriented Design

The project follows core OOP principles:

Encapsulation: Private fields with public getters/setters

Inheritance: Child class extends User

Polymorphism: Role-based behavior via User.Role

Separation of Concerns: Model, UI, and Persistence layers

